ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.249                Enzyme
NAME        delphinidin 3',5'-O-glucosyltransferase;
            UDP-glucose:anthocyanin 3',5'-O-glucosyltransferase;
            UA3'5'GZ
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-glucose:delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside 3'-O-glucosyltransferase
REACTION    2 UDP-glucose + delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside = 2 UDP + delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3',5'-di-O-beta-D-glucoside (overall reaction) [RN:R10063];
            (1a) UDP-glucose + delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside = UDP + delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3'-O-beta-D-glucoside [RN:R07913];
            (1b) UDP-glucose + delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3'-O-beta-D-glucoside = UDP + delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3',5'-di-O-beta-D-glucoside [RN:R07914]
ALL_REAC    R07913 R07914 R10063
SUBSTRATE   UDP-glucose [CPD:C00029];
            delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C16301];
            delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3'-O-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C16304]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3',5'-di-O-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C16303];
            delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3'-O-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C16304]
COMMENT     Ternatins are a group of polyacetylated delphinidin glucosides that confer 
            blue color to the petals of Clitoria ternatea (butterfly pea).
            This enzyme catalyses two reactions in the biosynthesis of ternatin C5: the conversion of delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside to delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3'-O-beta-D-glucoside, followed by the conversion of the later to ternatin C5, by transferring two glucosyl groups in a stepwise manner [1].
HISTORY     EC 2.4.1.249 created 2009
REFERENCE   1  [PMID:17668234]
